  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0dbb\u0ddd\u0daf \u0dad\u0dd4\u0db1\u0dda \u0d9c\u0db8\u0db1 \u0d9c\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dd2 \u0d9c\u0dab\u0db1\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The journey of the three wheels is fire",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "With the ongoing fuel crisis these days, three-wheeler fares have increased several times and some three-wheeler drivers are charging thousands of rupees.",
        "At present, the number of buses has also decreased, so people have to go to a hospital in case of illness as well as to go to a hospital in a three-wheeler.",
        "Singer Wisarada Abhishek Wimalaweera posted a note on her face book that a tricycle driver asked her for 3,000 rupees to go from Borella to Kollupitiya, and she went on her journey reducing it to 2,500 only.",
        "Actress Gayatri Dias also posted on her Facebook page that a tricycle driver charged her 3,000 rupees to go from Pannipitiya to Boralasgamu. Many people had responded to their notes, and those people had noted that they too had to travel in three-wheelers that fetched similar prices.",
        "5,000 rupees to go from Gallumuwadora to Maharagama, 8,000 rupees to come from Wellawatte to Navaloka, 30,000 rupees to go from Katunayake Airport to Moratuwa, 20,000 rupees to go from Negombo to Rajagiriya, 1,700 rupees from Armored Road to Colombo Fort, 1,800 rupees from Punchi Borella to Fort. They had mentioned that the three-wheeler drivers charged them Rs.6,000 to go from Piliyandala to Ratmalana, Rs.1,800 to go from Kurunduwatta to Colombo Fort, and Rs.4,000 from Kalubowila to Moratuwa.",
        "One person had stated that a certain tricycle driver requested 1,700 rupees for a trip in another metered tricycle that cost 450 rupees on the same day.",
        "It was also noted by one person that at the end of a journey promised for 9,000 rupees, the tricycle driver asked for a fee of 14,000 rupees.",
        "In this regard, when we asked a few tricycle drivers, they said that they had to queue for days to get fuel worth 2,500 rupees, and they had to pay between 2,500 and 3,000 rupees per liter of petrol to buy fuel without queuing.",
        "They also say that they cannot run cheap tricycles as they have to earn a living by getting fuel at such a price and driving the tricycle only once in five days. The three-wheeler drivers also say that if the fuel is received normally, they will be able to maintain the service at normal rates."
      ],
